-- Czech Official Arrested With $350,000 in Shoe Box, Lidovky Says
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-05-15T14:02:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/czech-official-arrested-with-350-000-in-shoe-box-lidovky-says.html
David Rath, a Czech regional governor
and a former health minister who was arrested yesterday by
police on bribery allegations, was carrying about $350,000 in a
shoe box,  Lidovky.cz  reported without saying where it got the
information.  Police, who also arrested seven other people for alleged
bribery, searched Rath’s home and office, the newspaper.  Rath is a member of the country’s largest opposition party,
 Social Democrats .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
